                          memory config.sys load himem first dos high umb keep files buffers modest preserve conventional                                                                 CONFIG.SYS memory                                               Load HIMEM first, use DOS HIGH UMB, keep FILES and BUFFERS modest, and preserve conventional memory.                                                                                            config.sys example himem dos high umb files buffers safe config sys baseline                                                                                    CONFIG.SYS example                                              Use HIMEM, DOS HIGH UMB, FILES 30, and BUFFERS 20 as the safe CONFIG SYS baseline.                                                                                                              autoexec autoexec.bat hygiene config.sys loads drivers first runs commands keep path short trim resident tools                                                  AUTOEXEC.BAT hygiene                                            CONFIG.SYS loads drivers first, then AUTOEXEC.BAT runs commands; keep PATH short and trim resident tools.                                                                                       batch file help exist checks clear status messages 8.3 dos-compatible names model files                                                                         Batch file help                                                 In a batch file, use IF EXIST checks, clear status messages, and 8.3 DOS-compatible names for model files.                                                                                      dpmi host protected-mode dos programs need such cwsdpmi.exe beside program                                                                                      DPMI host                                                       Protected-mode DOS programs need a DPMI host such as CWSDPMI.EXE beside the program.                                                                                                            copy hardware gpt2 model packs cwsdpmi batch files together before testing real dos                                                                             Hardware copy                                                   Copy GPT2, MODEL, PACKS, CWSDPMI, and batch files together before testing on real DOS.                                                                                                          config sys config.sys tuning himem.sys dos high umb modest files buffers values compatibility                                                                   CONFIG.SYS tuning                                               Use HIMEM.SYS, DOS=HIGH,UMB, and modest FILES and BUFFERS values for compatibility.                                                                                                             fat image full remove host-only training files grow disk assembly runs out space                                                                                FAT image full                                                  Remove host-only training files or grow the disk image when FAT image assembly runs out of space.                                                                                               hardware validation run same batch path real dos copy return.txt back compare checksums logs                                                                    Hardware validation                                             Run the same batch path on real DOS, copy RETURN.TXT back, and compare checksums and logs.                                                                                                      checksums dos sha-256 sidecars host compare file sizes checksum tool unavailable                                                                                DOS checksums                                                   Use SHA-256 sidecars on the host and compare file sizes on DOS when a checksum tool is unavailable.                                                                                             